{"lemma":"أَلْح","slug":"أَلْح","root":"ل.ح.#","root_slug":"ل-ح-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ل-ح-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n37586","n37591"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%92%D8%AD"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"jawbone, maxilla; chin","examples":[{"text":"يقولون عَثْنَنَ فلانٌ جَعَلَ من العِمَامة تحت حَنَكِهِ ويسمّونها العُثْنُون وبعضعم يسمّيها مَقْبِضَ سَطْلٍ. والصّواب تَلَحَّاهَا. يقال تَلَحَّى فلانٌ العِمامةَ إّذا جعلها تحت لَحْيِهِ. وفي الحديث أنّ النّبيّ ﷺ «أمر بالتَّلَحِّي ونَهَى عن الاقْتِعَاطِ». ويقال أيْضاً حَنّكَ. والاقتعاط أن تَلُوثَ العِمامةَ على رَأْسِكَ دون أن تجعلها تحت حنكك. يقال منه اقتعط يقتعط وهو المنهيّ عنه.","english":"They say that somebody ʕaṯnana – he applied his turban under the jaw, and they call the latter ʕuṯnūn and a part of them bucket handle. The correct is talaḥḥāhā. It is said that somebody talaḥḥā when he applied it under his jawbone. And in the Ḥadīṯ that the Prophet (PBUH) “ordered talaḥḥī and ended with iqtiʕaṭ.” One also says ḥannaka. And iqtiʕaṭ that you bind the turban on the head without applying it under the jaw."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of لَحَى (laḥā) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/laħj/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37586","headword_ar":"الحّ","root":"lH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iloHaAHN","text_ar":"اـِلْحَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a cloud)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rained continually,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incessantly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) Hence the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlH~ ElY $Y","text_ar":"الحّ على شى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v. infra]. (Msb) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlH~ Ealoyhi","text_ar":"الحّ عَلْيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iloHaAHN","text_ar":"اـِلْحَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He importuned him; plied him; plied him hard; pressed him; pressed upon him; pressed him hard; was urgent with him; persecuted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"harassed, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA@lomasoA^alapi","text_ar":"بِا@لْمَسْاَلَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Als~aw^aAli","text_ar":"فِى السَّوَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in asking, begging,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"petitioning;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloHafa","text_ar":"اَلْحَفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, L, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlH~ ElY gariymihi","text_ar":"الحّ على غَرِيمِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pressed his creditor perseveringly, assiduously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constantly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloHaHotu EalaY fulaAnK fiY AlAit~ibaAEi Hat~aY A@xotalafotuh","text_ar":"اَلْحَحْتُ عَلَى فُلَانٍ فِى الاِتِّبَاعِ حَتَّى ا@خْتَلَفْتُه"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I pressed upon such a one in following"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until I made him to be behind me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xlf","text_ar":"خلف"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlH~ EalaY $aYo'K","text_ar":"الحّ عَلَى شَىْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY $aYo'K","text_ar":"فِى شَىْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He applied himself to a thing perseveringly, persistently, assiduously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constantly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incessantly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlH~ fiY $aYo'K","text_ar":"الحّ فِى شَىْءٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He asked, begged,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"petitioned, for a thing much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"frequently;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though he stuck to it. (L.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlH~ EalaY gay~ihi","text_ar":"الحّ عَلَى غَيِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY gay~ihi","text_ar":"فى غَيِّهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He persevered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"persisted, in his error"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mdY","text_ar":"مدى"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a cloud)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stayed,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bimakaAnK","text_ar":"بِمَكَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a place;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alav~a","text_ar":"اَلَثَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (As, S.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlH~","text_ar":"الحّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was restive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refractory, and would not move from his place;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K;) like as you say of a she-camel"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaA^ato","text_ar":"خَلَاَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (As, S,) and of a horse and the like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hazana","text_ar":"حَزَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (As:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlH~t","text_ar":"الحّت"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did the same;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K;) accord. to some, and so used in a trad. (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlH~ti AlmaTiY~u","text_ar":"الحّتِ المَطِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The beasts of carriage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2653},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels, were fatigued, and became slow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tardy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlH~","text_ar":"الحّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a saddle of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qatab","text_ar":"قَتَب"},{"kind":"text","text":", L, K, and a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHol","text_ar":"رَحْل"},{"kind":"text","text":", and a horse's saddle, L)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wounded the back."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miloHaAHN","text_ar":"مِلْحَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","L","As"]},{"entry_id":"n37591","headword_ar":"اَلَحُّ","root":"lH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most, importunate, pressing, persevering,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xnfs","text_ar":"خنفس"},{"kind":"text","text":"; see the same article in the present work.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}